# Project Overview

Customer segmentation is an important technique that helps businesses understand their customers based on purchasing behavior. In this project, K-Means Clustering is applied to group customers into different segments using **RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary)** analysis. These customer segments can be used to create personalized marketing strategies, improve customer retention, and increase business revenue.

---

# Objective

The objective of this project is to analyze customer purchasing behavior and divide customers into meaningful groups using the K-Means clustering algorithm. The segmented customer groups help businesses identify loyal customers, regular customers, new customers, and inactive customers.

